## Stream Format (Locked April 7, 2026)

### Act 1 — Pre-Game Lecture
- Duration: 5–30 minutes depending on the myth. Let the material dictate.
- Content: What myth is being worked on, the creative problem being solved, relevant cosmological context
- Visuals: Canva lecture slides in the bottom content zone
- Scene: Lecture Scene
- Clip type: Mythology explainer / WriterTok education content

### Act 2 — Writing Sprint
- Duration: 15 minutes per sprint
- Goals: Stated clearly at the top of each sprint, visible on Notion goals panel throughout
- Writing environment: iA Writer Focus Mode — dark mode, narrow centered column
- Atmosphere: Cozy, quiet, focused. Mechvibes keyboard sounds. Outside Inn lo-fi music playing softly underneath.
- Scene: Writing Scene
- After each sprint: Debrief with community. Did the goal get met? Read what was written. React honestly.
- Clip type: Before/after craft clip, reading aloud, emotional reaction

### Act 3 — Debrief
- Verdict on session goals
- Read the best lines aloud
- Discuss what worked, what didn't, what comes next
- Clip type: Declaration moment, craft insight, honest reaction

### Gaming
> Bonus content only. Never a scheduled segment. If it happens, it happens after writing is done. WoW or variety — never locked to a single game.

